{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01YZD3evd2G9RDf1YPuM18kb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013Xv8emoosFzbRDEUL4VsS9","name":"mcp__planflow-mcp__planflow_remember","input":{"title":"Durable Object types & worker-export gap with adapter-cloudflare","content":"Two non-obvious things about the GalleryRoom DO (T3.1):\n\n1. TYPING: tsconfig deliberately does NOT add @cloudflare/workers-types to `types` (it would replace the DOM Request/Response/WebSocket globals the SvelteKit app is typed against). So the DO imports named CF types (DurableObjectState, WebSocket as CfWebSocket) and we added a narrow ambient file src/lib/server/worker-runtime.d.ts declaring just the two CF-only runtime surfaces we touch: the `WebSocketPair` constructor and the `webSocket` field on ResponseInit (for the 101 upgrade). The DO class intentionally does NOT `implements DurableObject` — that interface's fetch(CfRequest) signature clashes with the DOM Request used everywhere else; we cast only at the DOM↔CF boundary (stub.fetch(request as never)).\n\n2. PRODUCTION WIRING GAP: @sveltejs/adapter-cloudflare (4.9) generates _worker.js exporting only `default` (the fetch handler). It has NO option to re-export a Durable Object class. So although wrangler.toml binds GALLERY → class GalleryRoom, the built worker does not export GalleryRoom, and workerd warns: \"no such Durable Object class is exported from the worker\". CI build/test still pass (the class compiles and is unit-tested), but the DO will NOT actually run in production until the class is exported from the worker entry — e.g. a separate DO worker (Cloudflare's recommended path) or a post-build re-export step. This is a follow-up beyond T3.1's three-file scope.","type":"decision"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1039,"cache_read_input_tokens":84590,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1039},"output_tokens":56,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"249b1dfa-5fda-4826-8012-56dad82645fe","uuid":"73fd0c7c-3a01-480b-983e-9277a02dd3ba","request_id":"req_011CbRR2H15D3hP4VoCkzoHV"}
