{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01VPB7bmX9jMGZvsk3kcSS56","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SFmDVSfUq6xmMCHmrobrxW","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"PR_URL=$(gh pr create \\\n  --base master \\\n  --head task/T3.1-galleryroom-durable-object-websocket-hub \\\n  --title \"feat(realtime): t3.1 — galleryroom durable object websocket hub\" \\\n  --body \"$(cat <<'BODY'\n## T3.1 — GalleryRoom Durable Object WebSocket hub\n\nImplements the single Durable Object that holds every live-gallery WebSocket connection.\n\n### Changes\n- **`src/lib/server/GalleryRoom.ts`** — the DO hub. Accepts WS upgrades via the **Hibernatable WebSockets** API (`state.acceptWebSocket` / `getWebSockets`), so the DO is evicted while idle and billed only when messages flow. Exposes an internal `POST /broadcast` that fans the payload out to every live socket (skipping closed ones). `webSocketClose`/`webSocketError` keep the live set tidy.\n- **`src/routes/api/ws/+server.ts`** — `GET /api/ws` rejects non-upgrade requests with 426, otherwise forwards the upgrade to the single `GALLERY` instance (`idFromName`).\n- **`src/lib/server/gallery-room-name.ts`** — shared fixed room name (one shared gallery, no per-event sharding).\n- **`src/lib/server/gallery.ts`** — `broadcastToGallery()` helper for trusted server-side broadcast (consumed by T3.2).\n- **`wrangler.toml`** — uncommented the `GALLERY` binding (`class_name = \"GalleryRoom\"`) and added a `new_sqlite_classes` migration (required for hibernatable DOs).\n- **`src/lib/server/worker-runtime.d.ts`** — narrow ambient declarations for the two Cloudflare-only runtime surfaces the DO touches (`WebSocketPair`, `ResponseInit.webSocket`), avoiding a global `@cloudflare/workers-types` include that would clash with the app's DOM types.\n\n### Tests\n12 new tests (DO routing, upgrade 101, broadcast fan-out/skip/empty, close-code handling, the route, the helper). **56 tests pass**; typecheck and `pnpm build` are green.\n\n### ⚠️ Known follow-up (production wiring)\n`@sveltejs/adapter-cloudflare` (4.9) generates a `_worker.js` that exports only the `default` fetch handler and has **no option to re-export a Durable Object class**. So while the binding points at `GalleryRoom`, the built worker doesn't yet export it (workerd warns accordingly). CI build/test pass and the class is fully unit-tested, but the DO won't *run* in production until the class is exported from the worker entry — e.g. a separate DO worker (Cloudflare's recommended path) or a post-build re-export. Out of scope for T3.1's three-file contract; flagged for a follow-up.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nBODY\n)\")\necho \"PR_URL=$PR_URL\"\nPR_BASE=$(gh pr view \"$PR_URL\" --json baseRefName --jq .baseRefName)\necho \"PR_BASE=$PR_BASE\"\nif [ \"$PR_BASE\" != \"master\" ]; then\n  echo \"Fixing base...\"; gh pr edit \"$PR_URL\" --base master\nfi","description":"Create PR against master"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":493,"cache_read_input_tokens":88558,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":493},"output_tokens":54,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"249b1dfa-5fda-4826-8012-56dad82645fe","uuid":"02179840-dd0f-4e3e-9caa-b902008c3bc3","request_id":"req_011CbRR63zqqMRLHT4bVN7pB"}
