{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01KFj2Hm3W7abWPrSJ8q2MRi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"T3.1 is complete and merged. Summary:\n\n## ✅ T3.1 — GalleryRoom Durable Object WebSocket hub\n\n**Merged:** PR [#6](https://github.com/BekaChkhiro/demuri/pull/6) → `master` (commit `3d2b60d`), 0 recoveries needed.\n\n### What I built\n- **`src/lib/server/GalleryRoom.ts`** — the single DO hub. Accepts WS upgrades via **Hibernatable WebSockets** (`state.acceptWebSocket` / `getWebSockets`, so it's evicted while idle and billed only when messages flow), and an internal `POST /broadcast` that fans a payload out to every live socket (skipping closed ones). `webSocketClose`/`webSocketError` keep the live set tidy.\n- **`src/routes/api/ws/+server.ts`** — `GET /api/ws` returns 426 unless `Upgrade: websocket`, then forwards to the single `GALLERY` instance via `idFromName`.\n- **`src/lib/server/gallery-room-name.ts`** + **`gallery.ts`** — shared room-name constant and a `broadcastToGallery()` helper for T3.2.\n- **`wrangler.toml`** — uncommented the `GALLERY` binding (`class_name = \"GalleryRoom\"`) + `new_sqlite_classes` migration (required for hibernatable DOs).\n- **`src/lib/server/worker-runtime.d.ts`** — narrow ambient declarations for the two CF-only runtime surfaces (`WebSocketPair`, `ResponseInit.webSocket`), avoiding a global `@cloudflare/workers-types` include that would clash with the app's DOM types.\n\n### Validation\n56 tests pass (12 new), typecheck exits 0, `pnpm build` green. No lint script to run.\n\n### ⚠️ Known follow-up (flagged in the PR + saved as PlanFlow knowledge)\n`@sveltejs/adapter-cloudflare` 4.9 generates a `_worker.js` exporting only the `default` fetch handler, with no option to re-export a DO class. So the binding points at `GalleryRoom` but the built worker doesn't yet export it (workerd warns). CI passes and the class is fully unit-tested, but it **won't run in production** until exported from the worker entry — e.g. a separate DO worker (Cloudflare's recommended path) or a post-build re-export. Out of scope for T3.1's three-file contract.\n\n### Cleanup note\nI'm in the in-place worktree, so I didn't remove it. The dispatcher can run `planflow_worktree_remove(taskId: \"T3.1\")` if needed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":399,"cache_read_input_tokens":93820,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":399},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"249b1dfa-5fda-4826-8012-56dad82645fe","uuid":"5ca2efd4-4776-4a28-b8f9-7826750f9883","request_id":"req_011CbRRB3jrgwAtPeagV1Sh9"}
